{
  "texts": [
    "Notably, combining the predictions of both models in a confidence-weighted sum provides substantially higher accuracy than each standalone model, demonstrating the benefit of using diverse input representations for ML on diffraction data.",
    "We generated a total of 8000 simulated XRD patterns and an equivalent number of virtual PDFs from 28 and 45 crystalline phases within the Li-La-Zr-O and Li-Ti-P-O chemistries, respectively.",
    "These XRD patterns and their corresponding PDFs include 1400 single-phase, 2400 two-phase, and 4200 three-phase samples.",
    "Mixtures comprised of ≥ 2 phases were obtained through linear combinations of the single-phase patterns, from which virtual PDFs were computed via Fourier transform.",
    "Two CNNs were trained on each chemical space, as detailed in the Methods, and then applied to the simulated XRD patterns and virtual PDFs."
  ]
}